                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_fydbon" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fydbon</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fudbon</orth></form><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>несчастный день</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>unhappy day</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>плохая погода</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>bad weather</q></abv:tr></sense></sense><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>mæ walʒæg ærvyston fydbontæj</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>весну моей (жизни) я проводил в тяготах</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>I spent the spring of my life in hardships</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>31</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>jæ bontæ — fydbontæ</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ее (зимы) дни — тяжелые дни</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>her days (winter days) are hard days</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>126</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Из %r3%r<ref type="xr" target="#entry_fyd"/> | %ifud%i ‘дурной’ и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bon"/> ‘день’. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fydæbon"/>. Ант. %ixærzbon%i [см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xærzæbon"/>] употребляется в значении „прощай“, „прощайте“. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fydæxsæw"/>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From %r3%r<ref type="xr" target="#entry_fyd"/> | %ifud%i ‘bad’ and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bon"/> ‘day’. Compare with <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fydæbon"/>. The antonym %ixærzbon%i [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xærzæbon"/>] is used in the meaning ‘goodbye’. Compare with <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fydæxsæw"/>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>